A new government report recently released shows the nation's poverty rate was
virtually unchanged in 2007.  The U.S. Census Bureau's annual report also shows
the number of Americans without health insurance fell last year - the first
annual decline since the Bush administration took office.  But some economists
have criticized the report, saying it paints an inaccurate picture of the U.S.
economy today. VOA's Mil Arcega reports. 
 
 
 
 
 
 

